ign docs\n|   |-- spec.md\n|   |-- design.md\n|\n|-- session-routing/                # Router feature docs\n|-- session-store/                  # Store feature docs\n|-- sandbox-orchestration/          # Sandbox orchestration docs\n|-- workload-management/            # (implied from workloadmanager pkg)\n|-- ci-cd/                          # CI/CD design docs\n|-- deployment/                     # Deployment docs\n|-- idle-cleanup/                   # Idle cleanup docs\n|-- integrations/                   # Integration docs\n|-- python-sdk/                     # Python SDK docs\n|-- cli-toolkit/                    # CLI toolkit docs\n|-- testing/                        # Test manifest\n```\n\n**Key observation:** Neither `pkg/picod/` nor `cmd/` directories exist yet. They need to be created as part of AR-015.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The pkg/picod Module - Current State and Purpose\n\n**Current State:** The `pkg/picod/` directory **does not exist**. It is entirely unimplemented.\n\n**Purpose (from AR-015 proposal.md):**\nPicoD is a lightweight command execution daemon that runs inside each sandbox Pod. It:\n- Receives JWT-authenticated HTTP requests\n- Executes commands within a configurable workspace jail\n- Manages files (upload, list, download)\n- Provides a health check endpoint\n- Is the core component for AgentCube's code execution capability\n\n**Planned Package Structure (from proposal.md):**\n```\npkg/picod/\n|-- config.go       — Config struct, CLI flag parsing\n|-- server.go       — Server struct, NewServer, Run, route registration\n|-- auth.go         — AuthManager, JWT middleware, key loading\n|-- execute.go      — ExecuteHandler, command execution logic\n|-- files.go        — Upload/List/Download handlers, path sanitization\n|-- types.go        — Request/Response structs, constants\n```\n\nPlus a `cmd/picod/main.go` entry point.\n\n**Required Dependencies (from go.mod, already present):**\n- `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0`\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1`\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing tasks.md Files and Planning Documents\n\n**Task Tracking Convention:** Each AR (Architecture Request) in `changes/AR-XXX/` contains three documents:\n- `proposal.md` — Purpose, scope, architecture summary, impact analysis, acceptance criteria\n- `design.md` — Technical implementation details (architecture, data model, interfaces, error handling, testing strategy)\n- `tasks.md` — Granular task breakdown with checkboxes, verification criteria, task dependencies, acceptance criteria table\n\n**AR-015 tasks.md** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md`):\n- Currently contains **placeholder TODOs** (T1, T2, T3 all say \"TODO\")\n- Module: `pkg/picod`, Language: Go, Size: M\n- Precondition: Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n- Acceptance Criteria table with 4 items (AC1-AC4): compile, tests pass, no race, no lint warnings\n- Task dependency chain: `T1 --> T2 --> T3`\n\n**AR-015 design.md** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/design.md`):\n- Also contains **placeholder TODOs** throughout all sections\n- Gate Requirements listed (compile, test, race, no log.Printf, no sensitive data in logs)\n\n**AR-015 proposal.md** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md`):\n- **Fully detailed** — this is the most complete document\n- Contains full scope, architecture, route table, request/response structures\n- Impact analysis, risk assessment, alternative analysis\n- Detailed acceptance criteria with checkboxes\n\n**Reference tasks.md files with good patterns:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md` — Valkey store implementation (well-structured, 5 tasks T1-T5)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md` — Router implementation (very detailed, 21 tasks T-001 through T-021)\n\n**Other planning documents:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` — AR-015 Delta Spec with Gherkin-style scenarios (490 lines, very detailed)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md` — PicoD specification (179 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md` — PicoD design from source reference (245 lines)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` — TDD test contract\n\n---\n\n### 4. References to AR-015, ST-3, PicoD, and Command Execution\n\n**AR-015 references found in 163+ locations**, including:\n- All AR-015 documents themselves\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md`\n- Cross-references in AR-010/design.md (listed as future dependency)\n\n**ST-3 references:** All tasks.md files use `Stage ST-3 (Design) completed` or `Stage ST-3 (Design Complete)` as precondition.\n\n**PicoD references across the codebase:**\n- `pkg/router/jwt.go` line 25: `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go` line 53: `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go` line 273: `if template.Spec.AuthMode == runtimev1alpha1.AuthModePicoD`\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go` lines 567-618: `injectPicodAuthEnv()` function that injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` line 13: `AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"`\n\n**\"命令执行\" (command execution) references:**\n- AR-015 title: \"PicoD 命令执行 API\"\n- AR-015 proposal describes command execution via `exec.CommandContext`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Project Conventions\n\n#### Task Tracking Convention\nEach AR's `tasks.md` follows this structure:\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX — Title — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/xxx\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** S/M/L\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-XXX/design.md`, `changes/AR-XXX/proposal.md`\n\n## T1. Task Name\n- [ ] 1.1 Subtask description\n- [ ] 1.2 Subtask description\n**Verification:** description of how to verify\n\n## Task Dependencies\nT1 --> T2 --> T3\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n| AC1 | 编译通过 | `go build ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n| AC2 | 全部测试通过 | `go test ./pkg/xxx/... -v -count=1` |\n| AC3 | 无竞态条件 | `go test -race ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n| AC4 | 无 lint 警告 | `go vet ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n```\n\n#### API Design Patterns in Go\n1. **Gin framework** for HTTP services (used in router, workloadmanager, and planned for picod)\n2. **Handler structs with dependency injection** — e.g., `NewSandboxCreateHandler(deps *SandboxCreateHandlerDeps)`\n3. **Deps structs** for constructor dependencies (e.g., `LifecycleManagerDeps`, `SandboxCreateHandlerDeps`)\n4. **Response helpers** in `pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`:\n   - `JSON(c, code, data)` — wraps in `SuccessResponse{Data: data}`\n   - `Error(c, httpCode, code, message)` — returns `ErrorResponse{Error, Code}`\n5. **Request validation** via `Validate()` methods on request structs\n6. **Gin binding** with `binding:\"required\"` tags\n7. **JSON tags use camelCase** (e.g., `json:\"sessionId\"`, `json:\"exit_code\"`)\n8. **Error responses** use `gin.H{\"error\": string, \"code\": int}` for picod (simpler than workloadmanager's wrapper pattern)\n\n#### Package Organization\n- `pkg/` for library code\n- `cmd/` for binaries (not yet created)\n- Each package has its own `_test.go` files alongside source files\n- Constants in `constants.go` files\n- Types/models in `models.go` or `types.go` files\n- Response types in dedicated `response/` subpackages\n\n#### Logging\n- Use `klog` (k8s.io/klog/v2) for server-level logging\n- Use `log/slog` for structured logging in handlers\n- **No `log.Printf`** allowed (explicitly stated in gate requirements)\n- No sensitive data in logs\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Command Execution Patterns in the Codebase\n\n**There is NO existing command execution implementation** in the codebase. PicoD is the component that will provide this capability. However, the design is fully specified:\n\n**From `code-execution/design.md`** (derived from a reference implementation at `/tmp/agentcube-ref`):\n\n**Command Execution Handler (`execute.go`):**\n- Uses `exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)`\n- Captures stdout/stderr into `bytes.Buffer`\n- No stdin from client\n- Default timeout: 60 seconds\n- Timeout exit code: `124` (matching shell `timeout` command)\n- On timeout, stderr appends message with timeout length as integer seconds\n- Working directory resolved via `sanitizePath`\n- Environment augmented: `cmd.Env = os.Environ() + extra env vars`\n\n**Path Sanitization (`sanitizePath`):**\nFour-layer defense:\n1. `filepath.EvalSymlinks` on workspace\n2. `filepath.Clean` on input path, strip leading `/` if absolute\n3. `filepath.Rel` check — reject if starts with `..` or equals `..`\n4. `filepath.EvalSymlinks` on candidate, re-verify with `filepath.Rel`\n\n**Constants:**\n```go\nTimeoutExitCode = 124\nMaxBodySize     = 32 << 20  // 32 MiB\nPublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\nmaxFileMode     = 0777\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Patterns and Conventions\n\n#### Testing Framework\n- **`github.com/stretchr/testify`** — `assert` and `require` packages\n- **`net/http/httptest`** — HTTP handler testing\n- **`github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2`** — In-memory Redis for store tests\n- **`k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake`** — Fake K8s dynamic client\n\n#### Test Naming Convention\n```\nTest<Package>_<Function>_<Scenario>\n```\nExamples:\n- `TestNewJWTManager_NilConfig`\n- `TestAuthMiddleware_ValidToken`\n- `TestLifecycleManager_IsExpired_WithExpiresAt`\n- `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success`\n- `TestServer_Routes_HealthEndpointsPublic`\n\n#### Test Setup Pattern\n```go\nfunc TestXxx(t *testing.T) {\n    gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)  // or gin.ReleaseMode\n    w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    c, _ := gin.CreateTestContext(w)\n    c.Request = httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/path\", nil)\n    c.Params = gin.Params{{Key: \"param\", Value: \"value\"}}\n    \n    // ... setup mocks ...\n    handler.Method(c)\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n    // ... assertions ...\n}\n```\n\n#### Mock Store Pattern\n```go\ntype mockStore struct {\n    sandboxes map[string]*SandboxInfo\n}\n\nfunc newMockStore() *mockStore {\n    return &mockStore{sandboxes: make(map[string]*SandboxInfo)}\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *SandboxInfo) error { ... }\nfunc (m *mockStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error) { ... }\n// ... implements Store interface\n```\n\n#### Interface Compliance Check\n```go\nfunc TestXxx_InterfaceCompliance(t *testing.T) {\n    var _ Store = (*redisStore)(nil)  // compile-time check\n}\n```\n\n#### Table-Driven Tests\n```go\ntestCases := []struct {\n    name     string\n    info     *SandboxInfo\n    now      time.Time\n    expected bool\n}{...}\nfor _, tc := range testCases {\n    t.Run(tc.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n        result := mgr.isExpired(tc.info, tc.now)\n        assert.Equal(t, tc.expected, result)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n#### Environment Variable Testing\n```go\nfunc TestXxx(t *testing.T) {\n    original := os.Getenv(\"VAR_NAME\")\n    defer os.Setenv(\"VAR_NAME\", original)\n    os.Setenv(\"VAR_NAME\", \"test-value\")\n    // ... test ...\n}\n```\n\n#### Test Quality Gates\n- `go test ./pkg/xxx/... -v -count=1` — all pass\n- `go test -race ./pkg/xxx/...` — no data race warnings\n- `go vet ./pkg/xxx/...` — no lint warnings\n- Coverage >= 80%\n- T/C Ratio (test lines / code lines) > 0.4\n- Every `*.go` file must have a corresponding `*_test.go` file\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key File Paths\n\n| Purpose | Path |\n|---------|------|\n| AR-015 Proposal | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md` |\n| AR-015 Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/design.md` |\n| AR-015 Tasks | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md` |\n| AR-015 Delta Spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` |\n| PicoD Spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md` |\n| PicoD Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md` |\n| Go module | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/go.mod` |\n| Router server (pattern reference) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go` |\n| Router JWT (auth pattern reference) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go` |\n| Router middleware (pattern reference) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go` |\n| Router config (pattern reference) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config.go` |\n| Response helpers | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go` |\n| Handler constants | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go` |\n| AuthMode types | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` |\n| TDD Manifest | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` |\n| Reference tasks.md (AR-014) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md` |\n| Reference tasks.md (AR-009) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md` |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_287bc9906ffe9yItV7pRsPZvGu","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775839176438,"end":1775839395009}}}}
